visibility: SANDBOX
license: OFL
category: sans-serif
subsets: menu,latin,latin-ext

family: Capriola

designer: Viktoriya Grabowska

approved: true
description: <p>Capriola is a sans-serif \
  typeface whose unique style draws upon \
  forms seen in handwriting and italic types. Skeletons of the most \
  characteristic glyphs are inspired by quick handwriting and based \
  on a single hand movement (G,a,g,k,e). Capriola ambitiously seeks \
  push boundary of originality in the genre without \
  loosing a legibility.</p> \
  <p>The unusual glyphs are quite noticeable in large sizes which allows \
  for distinctive headlines. However in small sizes these gestures \
  become less noticeable making it possible to set longer texts. The \
  name "Capriola" means somersault in English. Such glyphs as "a", \
  "e" or "G" are the real acrobats and the "g" makes a double salto! \
  Capriola was spaced for web. Capriola's originality combined \
  with utility makes it ideal for a wide range of uses.</p>

font.Capriola-Regular.ttf.style: normal
font.Capriola-Regular.ttf.weight: 400

